CommonFields.Title: Non-covalently modified graphene sheets by imidazolium ionic liquids for multifunctional polymer nanocomposites
Author: Yang, Ying-Kui
He, Cheng-En
Peng, Ren-Gui
Baji, Avinash
Du, Xu-Sheng
Huang, Yuan-Li
Xie, Xiao-Lin
Mai, Yiu-Wing

ChooseParameter.Other: PMMA was purified by filtering over alumina powder to remove the inhibitors before use.

Mixing.Description: An appropriate amount of MMA monomer with 0.5 wt.% AIBN was added to the ImiG dispersion by magnetic stirring and the mixture was deoxygenated by vacuum/dry nitrogen for several cycles in a water–ice bath.
The flask, charged with the above reactants, was placed in a preheated oil bath at 70°C to perform free radical polymerization under a nitrogen atmosphere and constant stirring.

Cooling.Description: After a 12 h period, the black solution was poured into ice-cold methanol to produce a grey-black precipitate.

Drying-Evaporation.Description: The graphene was obtained by filtration and drying overnight at 70°C.

XRay_Diffraction_and_Scattering.Description: X-ray diffraction experiments were conducted in a D/MAX-IIIC X-ray diffractometer with Cu K-alpha radiation.

XRay_Photoelectron_Spectroscopy.Description: X-ray photoelectron spectroscopy was performed using a monochromatic Al K-alpha X-ray source.

Atomic_Force_Microscopy.Equipment: Digital Instrument Nanoscope IIIA Atomic Force Microscope

Thermogravimetric_Analysis.Description: Thermal gravimetric analysis was conducted using a TGA-7 Perkin Elmer calorimeter under argon flow (20 mL/min) at a heating rate of 20°C/min.

Electrometry.Description: DC conductivities were measured by a standard fourprobe method using a Keithley 4200 electrometer at room temperature.
